title: You Young Wins Bronze Medal in 1st ISU Grand Prix Event
text:
Figure skater You Young made a successful senior Grand Prix debut in Kelowna, Canada.

Yoo finished third with a total score of 217.49 points -- 139.27 in the free skate on Saturday and 78.22 in the short program the previous day -- in the Skate Canada International, the second of six events of the International Skating Union Grand Prix series.

Though she failed her first triple-axel jump in the free skate, she performed solidly in the rest of her routine, earning a podium finish in her debut event.

Russia's Alexandra Trusova took the top spot with 241.02 points, followed by Japan's Rika Kihira with 230.33.

Yoo's latest score is more than 16 points higher than her previous best of 200.89 points, and the fourth-highest score ever for a Korean female skater after those set by figure skating star Kim Yu-na -- 228.56 points at the 2010 Winter Olympics in Vancouver, 219.11 points at the 2014 Winter Olympics in Sochi, and 218.31 points at the 2013 World Championships in London, Ontario.
